cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with image representation learning using self-supervised tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also uses deep learning techniques to train a convolutional neural network (cs.LG) and introduces a novel self-supervised task (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the performance of the approach on classification and segmentation tasks (cs.CL) and discusses the robustness and transferability of the learned representations (cs.NE).
